Steps to perform an out-of-source build of gtest libraries.


-->  Create a build directory, copy configure.sh to it, 
     modify the copy of configure.sh as necessary 

%> cd $HOME/DAGMC/gtest   // the directory of this README
%> mkdir lib
%> cd lib                 

--> Run cmake 

%> cmake ../gtest-1.7.0

-- or --

%> ../configure.sh

--> Create the libraries

%> make

Now the fludag and meshtally unit tests can be compiled, assuming
the gtest libs in the ./lib subdirectory are referenced.
